description: Newport County have announced winger Jennison Myrie-Williams will leave the club after failing to agree new terms with the player.
title: Newport County: Winger Jennison Myrie-Williams leaves League Two club
title_page: Newport County: Winger Jennison Myrie-Williams leaves League Two club - BBC Sport
maintext:
Winger Jennison Myrie-Williams will leave Newport County after just one season.
Myrie-Williams, 29, will not extend his stay at Rodney Parade after both parties were unable to reach an agreement on a new deal.
He spent just 2016-17 at the club after joining from Sligo before that season began.
Myrie-Williams made 23 appearances with 14 starts and scored one goal, against Swansea Under-23s.
